Coronation Merchant Bank Limited on Monday closed its N10bn commercial paper offer. The bank, which was seeking to raise up to N10bn in the third and fourth series of its N100bn commercial paper programme, said the programme was intended to support its short-term funding requirements. The series three commercial paper has a tenor of 180 days and 14 per cent effective yield rate. The series three also has a discount rate of 13.10 per cent. The series four commercial paper has a tenor of 268 days, effective yield of 14.50 per cent and a discount rate of 13.11 per cent. Coronation Merchant Bank said the commercial paper had an ‘A+’ rating from Augusto & Co and an ‘A-’ rating from the GCR. The minimum subscription for commercial papers is set at N5m and in multiples of N1,000 thereafter. The bank said the offer opened on August 14, 2019 and closed on August 19. The allotment date was fixed at August 20, 2019. Copyright PUNCH.
